A state in the southern part of India. Karnataka is bordered by the Arabian Sea to the west, Goa to the northwest, Maharashtra to the north, Andhra Pradesh to the east, Tamil Nadu to the southeast, and Kerala to the southwest.
A panchayat town located in the Shimoga District of the State of Karnataka, India. It lies on the bank of the river Tunga and is also the headquarters of the Thirthahalli Taluk of Shimoga district.
A populated place. A city in the north Indian State of Uttar Pradesh, situated at the confluence of the Ganges and Yamuna rivers.
The capital of the Indian State of Karnataka. Located on the Deccan Plateau in the south-eastern part of Karnataka.

A state in the Republic of India situated in the eastern most part of the north Indian politico-geographical zone. Its capital is Patna. Bihar is surrounded by the Indian States of Uttar Pradesh to the west, Jharkhand to the south, West Bengal to the east, and has an international border with the Kingdom of Nepal to the north. Bihar lies in the fertile Indo-Gangetic Plain.
A populated place.
A populated place. A city in India that serves as the capital of two states, Punjab and Haryana, and is a union territory of India.
The capital of the Indian State of West Bengal. It is located in eastern India on the east bank of the River Hooghly.
A populated place. A city in the eastern part of the State of Uttar Pradesh in India, near the border with Nepal.
A state in southern India. It is bordered by Maharashtra, Chhattisgarh and Orissa in the north, the Bay of Bengal in the East, Tamil Nadu to the south and Karnataka to the west.
The capital city and most populous city of the Indian State of Andhra Pradesh.

A state located on the western coast of India. Maharashtra is bordered by the Arabian Sea to the west, Gujarat and the Union territory of Dadra and Nagar Haveli to the northwest, Madhya Pradesh to the northeast, Chhattisgarh to the east, Karnataka to the south, Andhra Pradesh to the southeast, and Goa to the southwest.
A hill station in the Western Ghats in the State of Maharashtra, India, about 3 km from Lonavala and 7 km from Karjat.
A populated place. A city in Ratnagiri district in the State of Maharashtra, India.

A state in the north-west of India. It is bordered by the Indian states of Jammu and Kashmir on north, Punjab on west and south-west, Haryana and Uttar Pradesh on south, Uttarakhand on south-east and by China on the east. Himachal Pradesh is divided into 12 districts. Himachal Pradesh is situated in the western Himalayas.
A tiny hill station in Shimla district of Himachal Pradesh state in India.

A State of India. Established 09-11-2000. Uttarakhand borders Tibet to the north, Nepal to the east, and the states of Himachal Pradesh and Uttar Pradesh (of which it formed a part before 2000) in the west and south respectively.
A populated place. A town in the Indian State of Uttarakhand and headquarters of Nainital district in the Kumaon foothills of the outer Himalayas.
The capital city of Uttar Pradesh.
A populated place. A town and a nagar panchayat (country subdivision) in Damoh district in the Indian State of Madhya Pradesh.
A populated place. A city in Pune district in the Indian State of Maharashtra.
A populated place. A city in the State of Karnataka, India.
A federally-administered Union Territory within the National Capital Region of India.
A city situated in the south west corner of Maharashtra, India. It is situated on the banks of river Panchganga.

A state in northwest India. The Indian state borders the Pakistani province of Punjab to the west, Jammu and Kashmir to the north, Himachal Pradesh to the northeast, Haryana to the south and southeast, Chandigarh to the southeast and Rajasthan to the southwest.
A populated place. A city in Ludhiana district in the Indian State of Punjab.

A state in India. It encompasses most of the area of the large, inhospitable Great Indian Desert (Thar Desert), which has an edge paralleling the Sutlej-Indus river valley along its border with Pakistan. The region borders Pakistan to the west, Gujarat to the southwest, Madhya Pradesh to the southeast, Uttar Pradesh and Haryana to the northeast and Punjab to the north.
A city on the banks of the Yamuna River in the northern State of Uttar Pradesh, India.
The capital of Rajasthan state, India.
A populated place. A town in the Indian State of Tripura.
